snippet.title: Back in Paris With Too Much Coffee
snippet.description:
Is it possible to drink too much coffee in Paris? I think so, but let's find out. Help me make better videos at http://patreon.com/jayswanson and then find me on the internet in all of the usual spots:
http://twitter.com/jayonaboat
http://instagram.com/jayswanson (me) 
Grab my guide to Paris here: http://bit.ly/ParisVloggersGuide
http://bit.ly/ShirtOfTheMonth (merch)
http://bit.ly/JaySwansonBooks (my books)
https://gum.co/camerafour (Disposable Camera Four digital scans)

Music by: Dyalla

My name is Jay Swanson - I'm an American writer living in Paris on an artist visa and hoping to make the city of light my home base - at least for the foreseeable future. I write science-fiction and fantasy, vlog daily, and love pizza a little too much.

Links below to Amazon are affiliate links - meaning if you click through them and buy something, I'll get some pennies. Thanks! (The FTC wants me to tell you that up front)

FAQ:
How long have you lived in France? On and off for over two years.

What do you miss most about ho- NACHOS

You're always talking about living on some ship. WHAT SHIP? - I made a "Draw My Life" video that explains a lot here: https://youtu.be/-MrvL37jTKM

Where are you from originally? - Pullman, Washington - a small university/agricultural town near Idaho (and yes, the potatoes are amazing).

What do you film with? - I currently film almost exclusively with my Samsung Galaxy S8: http://amzn.to/2lPKSpZ

How do you get those shots where you're walking or running? - A Joby Gorillapod for smartphones, like this: http://amzn.to/2sXNIL3

You drop your phone a lot, how does it survive? - THIS CASE IS AMAZING: http://amzn.to/2hoxgTA (Galaxy S7) - http://amzn.to/2Dt08Bu (Galaxy S8) - http://amzn.to/2FxVliP (iPhone)

What do you edit with? - Adobe Premiere - it's pretty much all I've ever used since high school.

Aren't you ever freaked out by leaving your camera behind to film yourself? - Yep. But not too badly - I tend to be careful when I do.

Why are you living in #Paris? - Because I've always wanted to; I feel at home here: https://youtu.be/4Vivf6MqMxQ

But what are you doing there? - Living it up! https://youtu.be/ZW2RP--DO8Y

Do you speak French? Oui. https://youtu.be/va1QjaHgij8

You talk a lot about the books you're working on, what are they about? - They're sci-fi (and fantasy) and I've got a decent pitch for you here: https://youtu.be/W2bKt4_Tp4E

Do you make money off YouTube? - Ha, no. I wish. It took me over 500 videos to make my first $100 off adsense. I think it will slowly change, but VERY slowly.

I really enjoy your videos, how can I support you? - The easiest and best way to support me is through Patreon, where you can pitch in as little as $1/mo to help me make better videos: http://patreon.com/jayswanson

I don't trust this Patreon thing - what's your PayPal? - Here's a handy link! https://www.paypal.me/jayswanson

I like PayPal in pink! - Here's my ko-fi if that's your thing (and coffee is your game): https://ko-fi.com/jayswanson

But I want to send you something tangible! - I do have a wishlist on Amazon, though it's a bit complicated with the international shipping situation. This is the US one: http://amzn.to/2ykS9Ux

And here's the French one: http://bit.ly/JaysFrenchWishList

Can I come stay with you in Paris? - Have you seen my apartment? It's too small for me as it is! https://youtu.be/6t2qj3rdyX8

OK, but how do I use the Metro when I'm there? - I made a handy video for you: https://youtu.be/T0YS5si8bJs

comments.textDisplay:
Love all the things. But seriously, I have been away and have a few weeks to catch up on here and I jumped into this episode because it looked fun. Gotta say, love the music, the new cinematic style with the new camera (could tell a difference right away) and I love Paris so those shots of Notre Dame pulled at my heartstrings.

Also, loves Bumblebee. My S.O. is one of the choristers in it. Not credited, but I know his voice anywhere. I think you will like it.

comments.textDisplay: My 2019 also got THE best possible start. ... . having such an amazing and nourishing experience right out of the gate like that really does make a body feel like this is a year when anything and everything is possible and I know EXACTLY what to do with that sort of energy.
